    "title": {
        "rendered": "Creating Your First Post Type"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>A step-by-step guide to creating a custom post type using Secure Custom Fields.</p>\n<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>SCF installed and activated</li>\n<li>Administrator access to WordPress</li>\n<li>Basic understanding of WordPress concepts</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Steps</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Access the Admin Panel</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Navigate to Custom Fields <span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-exclude-emoji\">\u2192</span> Post Types</li>\n<li>Click &#8220;Add New&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Basic Configuration</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Enter a descriptive name</li>\n<li>Configure labels</li>\n<li>Set visibility options</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Advanced Settings</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Configure permalinks</li>\n<li>Set up taxonomies</li>\n<li>Define capabilities</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Testing</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Save your post type</li>\n<li>Create a test post</li>\n<li>View on front end</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Next Steps</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Add custom fields to your post type</li>\n<li>Configure archive displays</li>\n<li>Set up custom taxonomies</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
